metadata.title: Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil
aws::graph::propositions: AS350 is a prototype variant of the Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil.
AS350 Firefighter is a fire fighting version of the Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil.
AS350B is powered by one Turbomeca Arriel 1B engine.
AS350 B1 is an improved version of the original AS350B.
AS350 B1 is powered by one Arriel 1D engine.
AS350 B1 is fitted with AS355 main rotor blades.
AS350 B1 is fitted with AS355 tail rotor with tabs.
AS350 B1 is fitted with a tail rotor servo.
AS350 B2 is a higher gross weight version compared to the B1 version.
AS350 B2 is powered by one Arriel 1D1 engine.
AS350 B2 has an aerodynamic strake fitted to tail boom along the starboard side.
AS350 B2 has an angled engine exhaust duct for better yaw control.
AS350 B3 is a high-performance version of the Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil.
AS350 B3 is powered by an Arriel 2B engine.
AS350 B3 is equipped with a single channel Digital Engine Control Unit (DECU).
AS350 B3 has a mechanical backup system.
AS350 B3 is the first helicopter ever to land on the summit of Mount Everest.

text:
## Variants

AS350
Prototype.
AS350 Firefighter
Fire fighting version.
AS350B
Powered by one Turbomeca Arriel 1B engine.
AS350 B1
Improved version of the original AS350B, which is powered by one Arriel 1D engine, type also fitted with AS355 main rotor blades, AS355 tail rotor with tabs and a tail rotor servo.
AS350 B2
Higher gross weight version powered by one Arriel 1D1 engine over the B1 version with aerodynamic strake fitted to tail boom along the starboard side and angled engine exhaust duct for better yaw control.
AS350 B3
High-performance version, is powered by an Arriel 2B engine equipped with a single channel Digital Engine Control Unit (DECU) with a mechanical backup system. This helicopter is the first ever to land on the summit of Mount Everest.
